Note:
Master Test Runner for All Advanced Memory Modules

Coordinates and executes comprehensive test suites for all 14 memory modules:
- AI Tuning - ML-based memory optimization and tuning
- Allocator Visualization - Memory allocator debugging and monitoring
- Custom Allocators - Arena, pool, slab, stack, region, and hybrid allocators
- Distributed Memory - Cross-system memory management and coordination
- FFI Bridge - Foreign function interface memory bridging
- GC Algorithms - Garbage collection algorithm implementations
- GC Visualization - Garbage collection monitoring and visualization
- Live Hot Swapping - Memory hot swapping capabilities
- Memory Layout - Memory layout optimization and analysis
- Memory Profiling - Advanced memory profiling and analysis
- Memory Safety Analysis - Memory safety validation and security
- NUMA Support - Non-Uniform Memory Access support
- Object Pool - Object pool memory management
- Ownership - Memory ownership and borrowing system

Provides comprehensive reporting, performance metrics, and production readiness validation.
:End Note

Import "./test_ai_tuning" as AITuningTests
Import "./test_allocator_visualization" as AllocatorVisualizationTests
Import "./test_custom_allocators" as CustomAllocatorsTests
Import "./test_distributed_memory" as DistributedMemoryTests
Import "./test_ffi_bridge" as FFIBridgeTests
Import "./test_gc_algorithms" as GCAlgorithmsTests
Import "./test_gc_visualization" as GCVisualizationTests
Import "./test_live_hot_swapping" as LiveHotSwappingTests
Import "./test_memory_layout" as MemoryLayoutTests
Import "./test_memory_profiling" as MemoryProfilingTests
Import "./test_memory_safety_analysis" as MemorySafetyTests
Import "./test_numa_support" as NUMASupportTests
Import "./test_object_pool" as ObjectPoolTests
Import "./test_ownership" as OwnershipTests
Import "../../../src/stdlib/advanced/utilities/common" as Common

Note: Test Suite Registry
Type called "TestSuite":
    name as String
    description as String
    test_runner as Function
    category as String
    priority as Integer
    estimated_duration_ms as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "TestResults":
    suite_name as String
    total_tests as Integer
    passed_tests as Integer
    failed_tests as Integer
    execution_time_ms as Float
    success_rate as Float
    errors as List[String]
    performance_metrics as Dictionary[String, Float]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "MasterTestReport":
    total_suites as Integer
    executed_suites as Integer
    total_tests as Integer
    total_passed as Integer
    total_failed as Integer
    overall_success_rate as Float
    total_execution_time_ms as Float
    suite_results as List[TestResults]
    performance_summary as Dictionary[String, Float]
    recommendations as List[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Test Configuration
Let PARALLEL_EXECUTION be true
Let DETAILED_REPORTING be true
Let PERFORMANCE_BENCHMARKING be true
Let ERROR_TOLERANCE_THRESHOLD be 0.95

Note: Test Suite Definitions
Let test_suites be [
    TestSuite with:
        name as "AI Tuning"
        description as "ML-based memory optimization and tuning tests"
        test_runner as AITuningTests.run_all_ai_tuning_tests
        category as "optimization"
        priority as 1
        estimated_duration_ms as 30000
        metadata as dictionary with "ml_enabled" as true,
    
    TestSuite with:
        name as "Allocator Visualization"
        description as "Memory allocator debugging and monitoring tests"
        test_runner as AllocatorVisualizationTests.run_all_allocator_visualization_tests
        category as "debugging"
        priority as 2
        estimated_duration_ms as 25000
        metadata as dictionary with "visualization_enabled" as true,
    
    TestSuite with:
        name as "Custom Allocators"
        description as "All custom allocator implementation tests"
        test_runner as CustomAllocatorsTests.run_all_custom_allocators_tests
        category as "core"
        priority as 1
        estimated_duration_ms as 35000
        metadata as dictionary with "allocator_types" as ["arena", "pool", "slab", "stack", "region", "hybrid"],
    
    TestSuite with:
        name as "Distributed Memory"
        description as "Cross-system memory management tests"
        test_runner as DistributedMemoryTests.run_all_distributed_memory_tests
        category as "distributed"
        priority as 2
        estimated_duration_ms as 40000
        metadata as dictionary with "network_required" as true,
    
    TestSuite with:
        name as "FFI Bridge"
        description as "Foreign function interface memory bridging tests"
        test_runner as FFIBridgeTests.run_all_ffi_bridge_tests
        category as "interop"
        priority as 2
        estimated_duration_ms as 20000
        metadata as dictionary with "ffi_languages" as ["c", "cpp", "rust"],
    
    TestSuite with:
        name as "GC Algorithms"
        description as "Garbage collection algorithm implementation tests"
        test_runner as GCAlgorithmsTests.run_all_gc_algorithms_tests
        category as "core"
        priority as 1
        estimated_duration_ms as 45000
        metadata as dictionary with "gc_types" as ["mark_sweep", "generational", "incremental", "concurrent"],
    
    TestSuite with:
        name as "GC Visualization"
        description as "Garbage collection visualization and monitoring tests"
        test_runner as GCVisualizationTests.run_all_gc_visualization_tests
        category as "visualization"
        priority as 2
        estimated_duration_ms as 30000
        metadata as dictionary with "visualization_formats" as ["json", "svg", "png", "html"],
    
    TestSuite with:
        name as "Live Hot Swapping"
        description as "Live memory hot swapping capability tests"
        test_runner as LiveHotSwappingTests.run_all_live_hot_swapping_tests
        category as "production"
        priority as 1
        estimated_duration_ms as 35000
        metadata as dictionary with "zero_downtime" as true,
    
    TestSuite with:
        name as "Memory Layout"
        description as "Memory layout optimization and analysis tests"
        test_runner as MemoryLayoutTests.run_all_memory_layout_tests
        category as "optimization"
        priority as 2
        estimated_duration_ms as 25000
        metadata as dictionary with "cache_optimization" as true,
    
    TestSuite with:
        name as "Memory Profiling"
        description as "Advanced memory profiling and analysis tests"
        test_runner as MemoryProfilingTests.run_all_memory_profiling_tests
        category as "profiling"
        priority as 1
        estimated_duration_ms as 40000
        metadata as dictionary with "real_time_tracking" as true,
    
    TestSuite with:
        name as "NUMA Support"
        description as "Non-Uniform Memory Access support tests"
        test_runner as NUMASupportTests.run_all_numa_support_tests
        category as "performance"
        priority as 2
        estimated_duration_ms as 30000
        metadata as dictionary with "cross_platform" as true,
    
    TestSuite with:
        name as "Memory Safety Analysis"
        description as "Memory safety validation and security tests"
        test_runner as MemorySafetyTests.run_all_memory_safety_tests
        category as "safety"
        priority as 1
        estimated_duration_ms as 15000
        metadata as dictionary with "security_critical" as true,
    
    TestSuite with:
        name as "Object Pool"
        description as "Object pool memory management tests"
        test_runner as ObjectPoolTests.run_all_object_pool_tests
        category as "core"
        priority as 2
        estimated_duration_ms as 10000
        metadata as dictionary with "pool_types" as ["fixed", "dynamic", "thread_local"],
    
    TestSuite with:
        name as "Ownership"
        description as "Memory ownership and borrowing system tests"
        test_runner as OwnershipTests.run_all_ownership_tests
        category as "core"
        priority as 1
        estimated_duration_ms as 20000
        metadata as dictionary with "ownership_model" as "rust_inspired"
]

Note: Test Execution Functions

Process called "execute_test_suite" that takes suite as TestSuite returns TestResults:
    Display "Executing test suite: " plus suite.name
    Display "Description: " plus suite.description
    Display "Estimated duration: " plus (suite.estimated_duration_ms divided by 1000) plus " seconds"
    
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
    
    Try:
        Let suite_results be suite.test_runner()
        Let end_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
        Let execution_time be end_time minus start_time
        
        Return TestResults with:
            suite_name as suite.name
            total_tests as suite_results["total_tests"]
            passed_tests as suite_results["passed_tests"]
            failed_tests as suite_results["failed_tests"]
            execution_time_ms as execution_time
            success_rate as suite_results["success_rate"]
            errors as list containing
            performance_metrics as dictionary with "avg_test_time_ms" as (execution_time divided by suite_results["total_tests"])
            metadata as suite.metadata
            
    Catch error:
        Let end_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
        Let execution_time be end_time minus start_time
        
        Display "ERROR in test suite " plus suite.name plus ": " plus error.message
        
        Return TestResults with:
            suite_name as suite.name
            total_tests as 0
            passed_tests as 0
            failed_tests as 1
            execution_time_ms as execution_time
            success_rate as 0.0
            errors as [error.message]
            performance_metrics as dictionary containing
            metadata as suite.metadata

Process called "execute_all_test_suites" returns MasterTestReport:
    Display "=========================================="
    Display "RUNA ADVANCED MEMORY LIBRARY TEST SUITE"
    Display "=========================================="
    Display "Executing comprehensive tests for all memory modules..."
    Display ""
    
    Let master_start_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
    Let all_suite_results be list containing
    Let total_tests be 0
    Let total_passed be 0
    Let total_failed be 0
    
    Note: Sort suites by priority (lower number = higher priority)
    Let sorted_suites be sort_test_suites_by_priority(test_suites)
    
    For suite in sorted_suites:
        Display "----------------------------------------"
        
        Let suite_result be execute_test_suite with suite as suite
        Let all_suite_results be all_suite_results with suite_result added
        
        Set total_tests to total_tests plus suite_result.total_tests
        Set total_passed to total_passed plus suite_result.passed_tests
        Set total_failed to total_failed plus suite_result.failed_tests
        
        Display "Suite completed: " plus suite_result.suite_name
        Display "  Tests: " plus suite_result.passed_tests plus "/" plus suite_result.total_tests plus " passed"
        Display "  Success rate: " plus (suite_result.success_rate multiplied by 100) plus "%"
        Display "  Execution time: " plus (suite_result.execution_time_ms divided by 1000) plus " seconds"
        Display ""
    
    Let master_end_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
    Let total_execution_time be master_end_time minus master_start_time
    Let overall_success_rate be total_passed divided by total_tests
    
    Let performance_summary be generate_performance_summary(all_suite_results)
    Let recommendations be generate_recommendations(all_suite_results, overall_success_rate)
    
    Return MasterTestReport with:
        total_suites as test_suites.length
        executed_suites as all_suite_results.length
        total_tests as total_tests
        total_passed as total_passed
        total_failed as total_failed
        overall_success_rate as overall_success_rate
        total_execution_time_ms as total_execution_time
        suite_results as all_suite_results
        performance_summary as performance_summary
        recommendations as recommendations
        metadata as dictionary with "execution_timestamp" as Common.get_current_time_ms()

Process called "sort_test_suites_by_priority" that takes suites as List[TestSuite] returns List[TestSuite]:
    Note: Simple bubble sort by priority (in a production system, use a more efficient algorithm)
    Let sorted_suites be suites
    
    For i from 0 to (suites.length minus 2):
        For j from 0 to (suites.length minus 2 minus i):
            If sorted_suites[j].priority is greater than sorted_suites[j plus 1].priority:
                Let temp be sorted_suites[j]
                Set sorted_suites[j] to sorted_suites[j plus 1]
                Set sorted_suites[j plus 1] to temp
    
    Return sorted_suites

Process called "generate_performance_summary" that takes suite_results as List[TestResults] returns Dictionary[String, Float]:
    Let total_execution_time be 0.0
    Let fastest_suite_time be 999999.0
    Let slowest_suite_time be 0.0
    Let total_test_count be 0
    
    For result in suite_results:
        Set total_execution_time to total_execution_time plus result.execution_time_ms
        Set total_test_count to total_test_count plus result.total_tests
        
        If result.execution_time_ms is less than fastest_suite_time:
            Set fastest_suite_time to result.execution_time_ms
        
        If result.execution_time_ms is greater than slowest_suite_time:
            Set slowest_suite_time to result.execution_time_ms
    
    Let average_suite_time be total_execution_time divided by suite_results.length
    Let average_test_time be total_execution_time divided by total_test_count
    
    Return Dictionary[String, Float] with:
        "total_execution_time_ms" as total_execution_time
        "average_suite_time_ms" as average_suite_time
        "fastest_suite_time_ms" as fastest_suite_time
        "slowest_suite_time_ms" as slowest_suite_time
        "average_test_time_ms" as average_test_time
        "tests_per_second" as (total_test_count divided by (total_execution_time divided by 1000))

Process called "generate_recommendations" that takes suite_results as List[TestResults] and overall_success_rate as Float returns List[String]:
    Let recommendations be list containing
    
    If overall_success_rate is less than ERROR_TOLERANCE_THRESHOLD:
        Let recommendations be recommendations with "CRITICAL: Overall test success rate is below acceptable threshold. Immediate attention required." added
    
    Note: Check for failed suites
    For result in suite_results:
        If result.success_rate is less than 0.8:
            Let recommendations be recommendations with ("WARNING: " plus result.suite_name plus " has low success rate. Review failed tests.") added
        
        If result.execution_time_ms is greater than (result.total_tests multiplied by 100):
            Let recommendations be recommendations with ("PERFORMANCE: " plus result.suite_name plus " is running slower than expected. Consider optimization.") added
    
    Note: Positive recommendations
    If overall_success_rate is greater than 0.95:
        Let recommendations be recommendations with "EXCELLENT: Memory library test suite is performing well. Ready for production." added
    
    If recommendations.length is equal to 0:
        Let recommendations be recommendations with "All test suites are performing within acceptable parameters." added
    
    Return recommendations

Process called "display_master_test_report" that takes report as MasterTestReport:
    Display "=========================================="
    Display "MASTER TEST REPORT - MEMORY LIBRARY"
    Display "=========================================="
    Display ""
    
    Display "EXECUTION SUMMARY:"
    Display "  Total test suites: " plus report.total_suites
    Display "  Executed suites: " plus report.executed_suites
    Display "  Total tests: " plus report.total_tests
    Display "  Passed tests: " plus report.total_passed
    Display "  Failed tests: " plus report.total_failed
    Display "  Overall success rate: " plus (report.overall_success_rate multiplied by 100) plus "%"
    Display "  Total execution time: " plus (report.total_execution_time_ms divided by 1000) plus " seconds"
    Display ""
    
    Display "PERFORMANCE METRICS:"
    Display "  Average suite time: " plus (report.performance_summary["average_suite_time_ms"] divided by 1000) plus " seconds"
    Display "  Average test time: " plus report.performance_summary["average_test_time_ms"] plus " ms"
    Display "  Tests per second: " plus report.performance_summary["tests_per_second"]
    Display ""
    
    Display "SUITE-BY-SUITE RESULTS:"
    For result in report.suite_results:
        Let status_icon be if result.success_rate is greater than 0.9 then "✓" else if result.success_rate is greater than 0.7 then "⚠" else "✗"
        Display "  " plus status_icon plus " " plus result.suite_name plus ": " plus result.passed_tests plus "/" plus result.total_tests plus " (" plus (result.success_rate multiplied by 100) plus "%)"
    Display ""
    
    Display "RECOMMENDATIONS:"
    For recommendation in report.recommendations:
        Display "  • " plus recommendation
    Display ""
    
    If report.overall_success_rate is greater than ERROR_TOLERANCE_THRESHOLD:
        Display "🎉 MEMORY LIBRARY TEST SUITE: PASSED"
        Display "The Runa advanced memory library is ready for production use."
    Otherwise:
        Display "❌ MEMORY LIBRARY TEST SUITE: FAILED"
        Display "Critical issues detected. Review failed tests before production deployment."
    
    Display "=========================================="

Process called "run_memory_test_validation" returns Boolean:
    Display "Running memory test validation..."
    
    Note: Validate test environment
    Let environment_check be validate_test_environment()
    If not environment_check.valid:
        Display "Environment validation failed: " plus environment_check.error
        Return false
    
    Note: Execute comprehensive test suite
    Let master_report be execute_all_test_suites()
    
    Note: Display results
    display_master_test_report with report as master_report
    
    Note: Return overall success
    Return master_report.overall_success_rate is greater than ERROR_TOLERANCE_THRESHOLD

Process called "validate_test_environment" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Note: Check required modules are available
        Let ai_tuning_available be AITuningTests is not null
        Let allocator_viz_available be AllocatorVisualizationTests is not null
        Let custom_allocators_available be CustomAllocatorsTests is not null
        
        Note: Check system resources
        Let memory_available be Common.get_available_memory() is greater than 100000000  Note: 100MB minimum
        Let disk_space_available be Common.get_available_disk_space() is greater than 1000000000  Note: 1GB minimum
        
        Let all_checks_passed be ai_tuning_available and allocator_viz_available and custom_allocators_available and memory_available and disk_space_available
        
        If all_checks_passed:
            Return Dictionary[String, Any] with "valid" as true and "error" as ""
        Otherwise:
            Return Dictionary[String, Any] with "valid" as false and "error" as "Insufficient system resources or missing modules"
            
    Catch error:
        Return Dictionary[String, Any] with "valid" as false and "error" as error.message

Note: Main Test Execution

Process called "run_all_memory_tests" returns MasterTestReport:
    Note: Execute comprehensive memory test suite for integration with advanced test runner
    Display "Starting comprehensive memory library test execution..."
    
    Let master_report be execute_all_test_suites()
    
    Display "Memory test suite completed:"
    Display "  Total Tests: " plus master_report.total_tests
    Display "  Passed: " plus master_report.total_passed
    Display "  Failed: " plus master_report.total_failed
    Display "  Success Rate: " plus (master_report.overall_success_rate multiplied by 100) plus "%"
    
    Return master_report

Process called "main" returns Boolean:
    Display "Starting Runa Advanced Memory Library Comprehensive Test Suite..."
    Display "This will test all 14 memory modules for production readiness."
    Display ""
    
    Let test_result be run_memory_test_validation()
    
    If test_result:
        Display ""
        Display "✅ MEMORY LIBRARY COMPREHENSIVE TEST: SUCCESS"
        Display "All memory modules are tested and ready for production use."
    Otherwise:
        Display ""
        Display "❌ MEMORY LIBRARY COMPREHENSIVE TEST: FAILURE"
        Display "Critical issues detected in memory modules. Review and fix before production."
    
    Return test_result

Note: Export results for CI/CD integration
Process called "export_test_results_for_ci" that takes report as MasterTestReport returns String:
    Note: Export in JSON format for CI/CD systems
    Let json_report be format_as_json(report)
    Let filename be "memory_test_results_" plus Common.get_timestamp() plus ".json"
    
    Write_file with path as filename and content as json_report
    
    Return filename

Note: Execute comprehensive memory tests
Let test_execution_result be main()